Subject: Re: [T2] weird oil cooler

Thanks for the picture. That one's a keeper. I think
it would work quite well for its limited surface area.
Next step would be to have a few thousand copper
"washers" die cut and slipped over the tube for
additional surface area! It will not diminish oil
pressure to the engine and except in already marginal
cooling situations, it should be above the curve on
positive vs negative cooling. -BaH

