 Now, is it just me or is this thing going to require
 major oil  
 pressure to keep oil flowing through it with all the
 bends and drag  
 from the tubing?
 
 But even when you find a way to keep the pressure
 up; the heat from  
 the oil is going directly into the stream of air
 used to cool the  
 engine. Which will make the oil even hotter....

 I think someone wasn't thinking clearly when they
 designed this.
 

